post_text: We are very sorry to announce that Weed Elementary School will be closed tomorrow, Friday, September 4th due to poor air quality. School should resume on Tuesday, September 8th as long as the air quality is healthy enough for students and staff to return to school. Please stay safe, healthy, and enjoy the extended four-day break. We love having kids back at school and building strong parent connections.

post_text:
WES families:
Our current air index quality is listed as "unhealthy" and is projected to be "unhealthy" for the coming week. With our COVID protocols, we have been directed to keep windows and doors open for as much ventilation as possible. With our unhealthy air, we would be drawing this back into the classroom and putting our students and staff at risk. We have made the difficult call to postpone the start of school for at least one week. We will provide an update by Friday, August 28th at 3:00pm regarding the start of school. Thank you for your understanding.

post_text: ATTENTION PARENTS: SINCE WE DO NOT HAVE A BUS RIGHT NOW, WE ARE ASKING PARENTS TO USE THE BUS LANE FOR DROP OFF IN THE MORNING SO THAT TEMPERATURES CAN BE TAKEN FOR YOUR STUDENTS. IF THEY ARE ABOVE 100.4, WE WILL HAVE YOU PULL INTO A PARKING SPACE AND WAIT 10 MIN TO RE-CHECK IT. IF YOUR STUDENTS' TEMP IS STILL HIGH THEY WILL NEED TO GO HOME. IF YOU WANT TO WALK YOUR STUDENT TO CLASS, PLEASE PARK AND GET TEMPS CHECKED BEFORE ENTERING THE CLASSROOM. WE ALSO RECOMMEND TAKING YOUR CHILD'S TEMP BEFORE LEAVING THE HOUSE IN THE MORNING.

post_text:
Weed Elementary School is excited to announce it is now accepting students for our Transitional Kindergarten program (TK).

TK is an exciting educational opportunity for your child to participate in year one of our developmentally-appropriate two year kindergarten program. Our TK curriculum is aligned with the California Preschool Framework standards and is taught by a fully credentialed elementary teacher. Our program develops a strong foundation for a lifetime of learning, and aligns with the WES reading program for kindergarten through third grade.

TK at WES is open to all students who will turn 5 between September 2, 2020 and September 1, 2021.

TK is a full day program at WES, and is offered during the same hours as our K-3 program: 8:30 am - 1:30 pm. Breakfast, lunch, and after school care are provided free of charge.

Space is limited to 16 students. Registrations received after this cap is met will be waitlisted. To register your child for Transitional Kindergarten, please call the WES office at 530-938-2715.

Dear WES Families,

In an effort to be proactive in the wake of recent international health concerns, Weed Elementary School will be switching our Spring Break from April 13-17, 2020 to now be March 23-27, 2020.

There is also a strong possibility that we will also be closing our campus beginning Wednesday, March 18, 19 & 20 as well as Monday, March 30. A notice will go out Monday regarding the District’s decision.

We will keep you updated via Remind, our school website and our weekly bulletin as information is made available to us.

post_text: February started WES’s celebration of multicultural months, celebrating all the wonderful, diverse cultures at our school. During the month of February, we celebrated the African American culture. In the classroom, students learned about the African American culture through literature and arts. Our amazing cafeteria crew prepared and cooked a cultural meal. Look for amazing artwork celebrating our communities diversity that will be displayed at local businesses each month. Weed Elementary School is excited to embrace, learn and celebrate our students, family and community’s different cultures.

post_text:
Mrs. Ramirez’s first grade...........
Hands on learning is the best kind of first grade learning! Our pumpkin unit began with a wonderful field trip to Papa’s pumpkin patch. Then we investigated, measured, graphed discussed, identified pumpkin parts, sorted and counted seeds by tens and ones. Of purse we did diagrams, art projects, and lots of writing. The highlight was making pumpkin pie filling from scratch, each child made their own miniature pie! We ate them and our baked pumpkin seeds at our harvest party!

post_text: WES had our first Cub Character event of the year! We had Chinese Acrobats that gave us an amazing performance! 89% of our student body qualified to go! Students who consistently show Cub Character and are invited to attend. This is a great learning tool and we’re headed to the movie theater in December and they all have a clean slate to start working towards that goal! Encourage your child to show positive character, let their teacher know what they’re working towards and keep modeling kindness, patience, self-control, respect and other positive traits at home.

post_text:
Yesterday was very exciting for some Weed Elementary students and the film production team highlighting the high elevation composting toilet at Horse Camp. The team filmed and interviewed students and their reactions to this innovative facility!

From Ms. Oberg: The students impressed our Sierra Club Guide and her boss with their knowledge of the Cascade Range! Several students were interviewed and filmed for an upcoming documentary about the composting toilet. Every single student displayed remarkable cub character. I was very proud of them all. Our Guide declared the students from Weed Elementary the best in the local area! WAY TO GO WEED CUBS!!

See you soon. 💚

post_text:
WEED UNION ELEMENTARY SCHOOL DISTRICT is accepting applications for the following positions for the
2019-2020 school year:

One position:
Instructional Assistants to work Monday - Friday, 8 hours per day. AA/AS degree or equivalent required.

Three positions:
Instructional Assistants to work Monday - Friday, 3.5 hours per day. AA/AS degree or equivalent required.

Application and salary information are available online at www.wes-weed-ca.schoolloop.com or at WES, 575 White Avenue, Weed, CA 96094 (530) 938-6103. Application deadline is Thursday,
August 1, 2019, at 4:00 pm.

post_text: It was an honor for me tonight to recognize Vickie Eddy at the Association of California School Administrator’s dinner as the Co-Elementary Administrator of the year for Siskiyou County. We love you Vic. 💚

post_text: Mrs. Ramirez’s first graders are working hard. They have done lots of hands on learning about the plant life cycle, plant parts and functions, and the water cycle. They just transplanted their seedlings to finish up their plant unit and started their water cycle unit with an awesome simulation. They created a cloud in a jar to demonstrate evaporation, condensation and precipitation. Then they saw how run-off and collection work with a playdough mountain and tin pan lake.

ATTENTION WES PARENTS AND COMMUNITY:

Tomorrow, Friday, join us to watch the Weed Elementary School Staff vs. the 8th grade students in a basketball game. Spaghetti dinner from 5:00-6:00 and gym opens at 6:00. There will be basket raffles and a Mini $100.00 and Grand Prize $400.00 WalMart gift cards. Also an awesome half time show. This is a great fundraiser. So please join us for a night of family fun!!
